They even named different streets.

00:49:56.230 --> 00:50:00.139
It was just like a little city.

00:50:00.260 --> 00:50:03.739
I was really thrilled to see brother brotherhood

00:50:03.739 --> 00:50:06.340
speak as the conventions I attended.

00:50:08.260 --> 00:50:12.900
I got married to Harold Miller in 1931.

00:50:12.900 --> 00:50:15.820
That was when the depression was going on.

00:50:15.820 --> 00:50:18.219
And times were very difficult.

00:50:19.500 --> 00:50:22.099
Everything was scarce.

00:50:22.099 --> 00:50:24.860
There were no jobs to be had.

00:50:24.860 --> 00:50:26.380
The food was rationed.

00:50:27.300 --> 00:50:29.260
People were really hungry.

00:50:29.260 --> 00:50:34.260
And they moved in any little shack that they could.

00:50:34.260 --> 00:50:36.699
Just to get by.

00:50:38.500 --> 00:50:40.019
We didn't have anything.

00:50:41.019 --> 00:50:44.739
And we couldn't drive the car.

00:50:44.739 --> 00:50:48.340
So we used to have a little white horse.

00:50:48.340 --> 00:50:52.230
The name was Lou.

00:50:52.230 --> 00:50:56.710
And we went out with the thing with the horse and buggy.

00:50:56.710 --> 00:50:59.469
She took us all over the place.

00:50:59.469 --> 00:51:01.469
Far distances.

00:51:02.469 --> 00:51:06.829
They would take this buggy and they would go 20, 30 miles.

00:51:06.829 --> 00:51:09.710
One direction, 20, 30 miles, the other direction.

00:51:09.710 --> 00:51:11.590
All the hard work that they put forth

00:51:11.590 --> 00:51:17.690
has resulted in several congregations in the area.

00:51:17.690 --> 00:51:21.530
We used to carry that magazine bag.

00:51:21.530 --> 00:51:24.809
We were witnessing for a while there.

00:51:24.809 --> 00:51:27.690
And so we put it around the horse's neck.

00:51:27.730 --> 00:51:31.210
And so the horse was taking part in our witnessing.

00:51:32.289 --> 00:51:34.610
People knew who was coming when they saw

00:51:34.610 --> 00:51:37.730
that little white horse come into their yard.

00:51:39.010 --> 00:51:41.369
Sometimes they just called.

00:51:41.369 --> 00:51:43.610
And I remember wearing two coats.

00:51:45.050 --> 00:51:46.530
Yeah, it's tiresome.

00:51:47.530 --> 00:51:48.730
But we were young.

00:51:50.449 --> 00:51:53.130
They would just go out regardless of rain or shine

00:51:53.130 --> 00:51:54.530
or whatever was going on at the time.

00:51:54.530 --> 00:51:55.570
And when they didn't have a car,

00:51:55.570 --> 00:51:56.369
